# ── Google Maps basemaps (optional) ──────────────────────────────────────────

# Enables "Google Satellite" and "Google Hybrid" as the default satellite basemaps

# (OpenLayers ol/source/Google — Map Tiles API, not XYZ tile URLs).

#

# Setup:

#   1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/google/maps-apis

#   2. Create or select a project → Credentials → Create API key

#   3. Enable APIs for that project:

#        • Map Tiles API          (required for Google Satellite / Hybrid)

#        • Maps JavaScript API    (optional; not used by the current tile source)

#   4. Restrict the key:

#        • Application restrictions → HTTP referrers (websites)

#        • Add your domains, e.g. http://localhost:5173/* and https://yourdomain.com/*

#        • API restrictions → restrict to "Map Tiles API" (recommended)

#   5. Copy this file to frontend/web/.env and paste the key below

#   6. Restart the Vite dev server (env vars are read at startup / build time)

#

# Without a key, the app falls back to Esri World Imagery satellite basemaps.

# Never commit real API keys to git.

VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=

